IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE IOWA CATTLEMEN'S ASSOCIATION IS TO PROVIDE ITS MEMBERS THE OPPORTUNITY TO ENHANCE AND FURTHER DEVELOP THE BEEF INDUSTRY IN THE STATE OF IOWA AND THE NATION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE IOWA CATTLEMEN'S ASSOCIATION IS TO PROVIDE ITS MEMBERS THE OPPORTUNITY TO ENHANCE AND FURTHER DEVELOP THE BEEF INDUSTRY IN THE STATE OF IOWA AND THE NATION.
IRS990.Desc: PROVIDE INFORMATION AND EVALUATION OF MEMBER'S COW HERDS AND FEEDLOTS TO ENABLE THEM TO MAKE THEIR CATTLE OPERATIONS MORE EFFICIENT AND PROFITABLE. THE ASSOCIATION COMMUNICATES WITH ITS MEMBERS THE MOST UP TO DATE INFORMATION ON THE BEEF INDUSTRY AND PROVIDES LOCAL COUNTY AFFILIATES WITH INFORMATION AND SUPPLIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part I-A, Line 1 - Direct and Indirect Political Campaign Activities
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION'S POLITICAL ACTION COMMITTEE'S CAMPAIGN ACTIVITIES ARE FOR THE SUPPORT OF POLITICAL PARTIES AND VARIOUS CANDIDATES FOR ELECTION TO IOWA STATE OR LOCAL OFFICE. THE COMMITTEE IS DEDICATED TO THE SUPPORT OF CANDIDATES WHO HAVE TAKEN RESPONSIBLE POSITIONS ON ISSUES INVOLVING IOWA AGRICULTURE.PART III - A - AS PROVIDED IN REV. PROC. 98-19 - SEC 4 SUBSECTION .02 THE IOWA CATTLEMEN'S ASSOCIATION, AN AGRICULTURAL ORGANIZATION TAX EXEMPT UNDER IRC 501(C)(5), IS TREATED AS SATISFYING THE REQUIREMENTS OF IRC 6033(E)(3) SINCE MORE THAN 90% OF ALL ANNUAL DUES ARE RECEIVED FROM PERSONS, FAMILIES OR ENTITIES IN AMOUNTS LESS THAN THE STATED MAXIMUM ANNUAL DUES ALLOWED AS INDEXED FOR INFLATION.

THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT BELIEVE IT HAS ANY INCOME DERIVED FROM UNRELATED BUSINESS ACTIVITIES. THE ORGANIZATION BELIEVES THAT IT HAS APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN, AND AS SUCH, DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH MEMBER OF THE GOVERNING BODY HAS ACCESS TO A COPY OF THE FORM 990 TO REVIEW BEFORE IT IS FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION REVIEWS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY WITH DIRECTORS ANNUALLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD REVIEWS THE COMPENSATION OF THE CEO ANNUALLY AND DOES COMPARISONS WITH SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, ORGANIZATION POLICIES AND TAX FILINGS ARE AVAILBLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON THIER REQUEST.
